Business Brief -- Bowne  Co.:
   Earnings Rebound Is Posted
   For Firm's Fiscal 1st Period
Richard H. Koontz, president and chief executive officer,
called the results "encouraging." He said, "Our business has
been very good when measured on a seasonal basis. Though our
first quarter is traditionally our slowest, low interest
rates and rising stock prices combined to create a very
attractive marketplace for both debt and equity offerings."
He added that prospects for the second quarter "look bright."